Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Recodify AOTO and ADO owner shorthand to AO and A4
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

AOTO was OTO, ADO was D4 — both changed to keep the branch-shorthand
scheme uniform (single-digit-suffixed two-letter codes: A1-A4, AO, CS).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01E4nFqBzkkZeasGtQc5zVum
